universe of origin : the teardown — a made machine, opened and explored
seal               : Mattel's challenger to the Atari 2600 led with a genuine 16-bit CPU, a graphics chip with proper backgrounds, and a speech add-on that made games talk. Its directional disc controller and overlay keypad were divisive, but 'Intellivision' — intelligent television — promised a step up in sophistication.
